Officially only open to students and staff at the university, though in reality there's nothing to stop anyone wandering in. 

Also be aware of the gender neutral toilets on the ground floor of the students union building, which are a 2 minute walk away.

comment: Doesn't always have regular open hours but GLO is a very safe place for the LGBT community.

name: Foster City Laundromat
directions: In the front by the card machines
comment: You need a laundry card to open the door but it does not charge you and you don't need to be a customer at the time of use.

name: LA Fitness
directions: First floor, across from the larger not-so-gender neutral bathrooms.
comment: If you don't have LA Fitness membership you can pretend you are interested in a membership and then ask to use the restrooms.

name: Panchero's
directions: Can't miss them - right in the middle
comment: No purchase necessary

name: Wagamama (Cardiff Library)
directions: You have to go up some stairs, but there's lots of stalls in a single bathroom, and some stalls are marked female, and most are marked neutral.
comment: It's a restaurant, so you've got to buy something! I recommend the donburi for a whole meal, but gyoza are good for a little fast snacky thing to take away.

name: Davidson Math and Science at the University of Nevada, Reno
directions: On the first floor across from the main lecture hall.
comment: Someone taped a piece of paper that says unisex to the door, so I don't know if it's permanent. But it's been there for over a week now so it's looking good.

name: Schulich Lecture Hall at the University of Nevada, Reno
directions: On the bottom floor near the pendulum, tucked into the corner.
comment: It is really really tiny. If you are a bigger person you might not be able to fit. I don't know who designed this, maybe it was an after thought, but you are almost forced to touch the wall while on the toilet.

name: The Overlook at the University of Nevada, Reno
directions: It's in the foyer before you actually go into where the food is.

name: Greek Jalapeño
comment: you have to be a customer, it is a sit-down and carry-out restaurant

name: Walmart Supercenter (in Springfield near Winco)
directions:
The Walmart Supercenter is located on Olympic Street, off Mohawk (past the Winco). The Walmart is in the same parking lot as the KFC and Jerry's Home Improvement. 

There are two gendered, multi-user restrooms at the front of the store by the checkouts, ignore those. The "Family" restroom is located in the rear of the store, near the shoe/luggage department. (to the left of the refrigerated groceries and Baby clothes, to the right of the electronics/media sections. - There's a large "RESTROOMS" sign on the wall). 

This area is like a second "Customer Service" area, and has three restrooms, a multi-user female, a multi-user male, and a single-user unisex restroom. All three are Wheelchair accessible.
comment: The Unisex restroom is a large, single-user restroom, which is definitely large enough for a wheelchair. This restroom seems to be very well maintained. In the evenings, this area is often cluttered with carts full of 'go backs' and such, but I believe the restroom is still accessible during the later hours.

name: Dollar Tree #1987 (River Road)
directions: The Dollar Tree is located in the shopping mall with Wendy's on River Road (Across from Bi-Mart/Grocery Outlet). Restroom is located on the back wall of the store, on the left-hand side as you enter the store. A key may be required depending on time of day.
comment: This restroom is a large, single-user, wheelchair accessible, unisex restroom. It is the only customer restroom in the store. It is not what I'd call "well maintained", and is generally not the cleanest it could be, because children use the restroom alone.Still, there is almost always plenty of toilet paper, paper towels, soap, etc.

name: Target
directions: Labeled "Family Restroom," right around the corner to the left when you walk in.

name: Starbucks, Dawson Street
comment: Must be a paying customer, the code to open the restroom door is on the receipt.

name: Blush & Blue
comment: Awesome lesbian bar. Totally cool with Trans* folks.

name: Starbucks, O'Connell Street
directions: Opposite the GPO, bathroom is in at the back, past the counter.
comment: Must be a paying customer, code to enter the bathroom is on your receipt.

name: Piney Wood Park
directions: A small shelter at the SE corner of the parking lot has a half dozen unisex stalls.
comment: These are not especially nice restrooms - concrete floor, small metal mirror, crooked toilet seats - but there is running water, they are cleaned regularly, and the location is safe.

name: Pret, regent st
directions: On the right of the counter, single gender neutral stall.
comment: Have to ask to go through, seems to be open all the time though.

name: Centerside I
directions: Just past the elevators on the right-hand side
comment: You have to park in the visitor parking but the first hour is free

name: Golding's Free Dive
directions: Behind the bar
comment: Licensed premises with two gender neutral bathrooms, one is large and has a wheelchair-friendly grab bar. Generally busy later at night.

comment: Have to be a paying customer

comment: Open to the public from 8 to 6 on weekdays.

name: Subway Restauraunt #59903 (Broadway & Olive)
directions: Just inside the main entrance, While standing at the order counter, the restroom is directly behind you.
comment: Restroom is for customers only. The restroom in this location is unisex, and is a large, single-user restroom with a locking door.

name: Austin Coffee
directions: Back of the shop
comment: No one here minds anyone using either bathroom, I've seen hipsters with beards that rival Gandalf's use the woman's restroom.

name: On street
directions: Near the corner of liebig st, small building on the footpath.
comment: Genderless automatic self cleaning

name: Saint Vincent dePaul Thrift Store (River Road/Division)
directions: The Saint Vincent dePaul thrift store is located on Division Avenue, off River Road near the Fred Meyer and Albertsons (just north of Beltline). The restrooms are located in the center-back section of the store, near the fitting rooms.
comment: The restrooms at this location are gendered, single user restrooms with locking doors. The women's room is a spacious, presumably wheelchair accessible room, with the tiniest toilet ever. (it's actually pretty awkward unless you're a child) The restrooms aren't generally well kept here, but if you have to go... it's an option.

name: Eugene Station - Lane Transit District
directions: Most buses lead to the Eugene Station, located on Willamette Street between 10th and 11th Avenue.
comment: Restrooms are located in the information and ticket sales lobby, and are thus only available during business hours. While LTD does offer traditional multi-stall, gendered restrooms in this location, they also provide a unisex-wheelchair accessible 'single user' restroom with a locking door.

name: Goodwill Industries Thrift Store
directions: Goodwill's thrift store is located on Seneca Road, just off West 11th, opposite the Fred Meyer parking lot.
comment: This store has only one unisex restroom open to the public, it is a single-user, locking restroom.

name: Burger King
directions: Burger King is located near McDonalds on Mohawk, on the same block as Winco, on the corner of Olympic and 18th Street
comment: Men's and Women's restrooms are both single-user, locking door.

name: TCU Brown-Lupton University Union (BLUU)
directions: First floor of the south wing of the BLUU, located behind the information desk next to the Campus Activities office.
comment: Two separate unisex restrooms available.
